reviews_data.review_text:
Love Manos, great food and great ambiance👌👌Would highly recommend it for anyone looking for authentic flavors. Their Bolognese tasted just like the flavors from many moons ago when we lived in CT..Μπράβο σας 🇬🇷 🇬🇷🇬🇷

We almost didn’t get a chance to dine in due to the large crowds as we left the  Stormers game, the evening was worth the wait. My kids literally cleaned out their plates..😋😋😋 Amazing service from Victoria.

Best spot in Cape Town, good is always incredible, drinks are quick and staff are all super friendly. Love Mano's and highly recommend the prawn starter, Greek pheasant salad, steak and chicken and pasta, and the creme brule and banoffie, actually everything is good - you can't go wrong!

Vaping in a restaurant is not acceptable. Every second table had people vaping. The outside smoking area is too close to the inside area and the whole area was just smoke and vapour.  The food was great but we won't be going back until they ban the vaping and smoking.

reviews_data.review_text: I have been to Mano's many times over the years! Its one of my favourite local spots in Cape Town. You always know what you are going to get! Consistency is key & they just get it right! I love their beef carpaccio, the best in town! Also highly recommend the chicken limone!

Space univiting. The service was extremely slow. It felt like one is ignored. Waitress immature, has to be reminded on what to do.  Chili dish dirty and not cleaned as though removed from another table. Food not appetizing. Bread burnt and hard. Nothing impressive
The salad was great, enormous for one.  The fish was excellent.

Nice Service but horrible food quality. I felt sorry for the ingredients that went into the Penne Salmone.
We also ordered Chicken which turned out to be super dry. Would not recommend if you value good food
Food was great. Ask for Joao's special filled. Beautifully prepared and super delicious.... it's not on the menu

Solid and reliable.
Consistently good.
Great service and food.

This restaurant is a first choice when coming to Cape Town.

For the last 7 years we’ve had excellent service and mouth watering food each and every time.

Waiters are professional and the manager also jumps in when the place is pumping to ensure it remains a 5 star restaurant.

Would recommend hands down to anyone visiting Cape Town, it is worth driving 30+ minutes for the top class experience.
The best is food,  good quality and menu. Very well located and nice ambience. Quite busy place.

review_questions.Noise level: Loud, but you can still talk

reviews_data.review_text: Some of the best food I've had in Cape Town. Would recommend it anytime.

The first night in Cape Town, the city known for its excellent restaurants, and then this... I can't recall the last time I was so disappointed. The calamari were unavailable, as was the rice for the shrimp curry – yes, rice. Initially not a big deal, but then a potato was served with the curry, making it completely impractical as the liquid curry couldn't be properly enjoyed. I ordered the octopus with spinach as a side. The octopus was rubbery, and the spinach seemed reheated, lacking any flavor, likely a frozen product. The curry was mediocre, and the shrimp didn't taste particularly fresh, probably frozen as well. Despite being avid food enthusiasts who appreciate quality, I simply cannot comprehend the positive reviews, especially when more than half of the meal was left uneaten. Furthermore, the price for this quality was simply unfair. Nonetheless, the service was very pleasant.

Absolutely delicious food with a great, buzzy atmosphere of people enjoying great food in good company! The staff were super friendly and efficient too 😊
Extra points for ice with my rose wine before even asking for it!
Edit.
Returned tonight, and the food and service was excellent again, thank you Claudia 😊
What a nice restaurant to sit down and enjoy a meal. Prawn curry was lovely.

Jade and Bella were superb hosts to a truly incredible dining experience. This place is always busy and rightly so. The class and proactivity of the Manager is part of the reason why this venue cannot be missed!  Needless to say the food was delicious!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Grilled Calamari, Tempura Prawns, Hot Chilli Sauce

reviews_data.review_text: One of my favourite lunch spots. Delicious food, great staff and fantastic people watching when you sit outside.

Usual delicious food. Generous portions and reasonable prices, although wine prices slightly inflated. I'm not being terribly PC, but mention must be made of the amazingly beautiful servers !!!! They would not be out of place in Vogue magazine :)
Service was excellent however the food a little disappointing as the halloumi and chips served with food was certainly older than should be. Certainly would try again

It is a matter of taste. The food was good and the service was excellent, it was very rowdy. I had the impression the women visit here to practice their loudest cackle. This was not just one evening but several.

Our hotel was very close so we thought we'd give Mano's a try for a bit of lunch, and were very happy we did. The food, drink and the service was A1. Kelly the owner even put herself out of her way to come and welcome us and had a little chat, lovely friendly lady for sure.
We thought it was that good we went back the following night. As we turned up, Kerry welcomed us again and also remembered my girlfriend's name and mine, which we both thought was amazing. Over the 2 meals which included amazing salads, piri piri chicken livers, tempura prawns, lamb chops, bbq chicken kebabs, spaghetti bolognese, black tiger prawns and lovely hot chilli sauce.
All the food we ate was absolutely awesome and would definitely visit again when back in town. The 2nd time we visited, the restaurant became very full, very quickly, so I'd highly recommend booking a table, we saw multiple groups being sent away.
Brilliant food and great hospitality puts Mano's very high up on my Cape Town restaurant list, maybe top!

An excellent lunch here exceeding expectations. Kob was super fresh and cooked expertly. Greek salad was authentically rustic with crisp, quality ingredients and the correct feta. Tables
Nicely spaced with attentive service. Could have been in the Med, great coffee and value.
Rude and arrogent. Food is average

Tasted chicken liver peri peri for the first time, and I loved it. I also ordered the grilled calamari, nothing to fault. My partner had issues with the grilled chicken since he didn't like to eat with his hands, but the taste was good. Great service, nice location. Overall, it was a great lunch.
Food is delicious but please install more of those acoustic panels
The Kobeljou was incredible
Under whelming.

I’ve been a loyal patron of Mano's since it first opened in Green Point, and over the years I’ve shared many wonderful moments there with family, friends, and clients. I’ve also recommended the restaurant to countless guests through my work in the service industry.

Unfortunately, the treatment I received over the phone today was deeply disappointing - unprofessional to the point that I felt compelled to visit the restaurant in person to address my concerns. Sadly, that interaction only reinforced my disappointment.

Mano, had you been present today,I would have shared my feedback directly with you, as I’ve always held both you and your restaurant in high regard. It’s genuinely regrettable to write this, but after more than 25 years of loyalty, I can no longer support an establishment that treats its patrons in this way.

Daniel
Awesome

A stunning venue, absolutely delicious food, their Fillet Prego Rolls are renowned. I had a fresh Kingklip, which was devine. My wife enjoyed their Penne Salmone and she was in 7th heaven. Their service is excellent and the food is really delicious and tasty. I will definitely be back for more.

Hidden gem of Cape Town dining scene. It has lost little bit of its old charm for being the family kitchen for the Sea Point and Green Point crowd, but the food is still excellent and they're still paying special attention to the ingredients. It's more of a restaurant now.

First time I was dining there, I met Paul Allen (R.I.P.) of Microsoft through a common friend. I suppose that sums up how the place is known for the IT crowd (See what I did there 👈😁).

Greek Peasant Salad is a must have for starters. That alone gets the place five stars.
I had the prawn curry as it came with high reviews. It was perfect 👌🏽 but just too expensive at 285 plus 15% vat. It also gets noisy.
Our absolute favourite. Very buzzy
No vegan options. Had to go to Woolies next door for a cappuccino with oat milk.

Overall very average experience due to the very average food. None of us thought our dishes were great, it was all just meh.
Service was good.

عجبني الحلا عنهم جدا

120 راند كلها
Is one of the best places for a girls night. Do recommend!!!

Wow, what an incredible experience at Mano’s. The fillet prego was tender and perfectly cooked and to top it off the Chocorico for desert was next level. Justine’s service was excellent and the manager Mandy is great! Will definitely be back soon 🔜

Good food, nice vibe, always a great evening. Tempura shrimp. Pork ribs. Frites, as always,  rated, 9/10, pretty good.  The spinach side was amazing, must have! No Mano tonight, too bad, Shaun is a wonderful host. Nice wine selection, Paul Cluver Chard reserve, turns out to have been a Platter 5*, was worthy! A must visit!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Tempura Prawns, Shrimp Tempura with Sweet Chilli Sauce

reviews_data.review_text:
Well established restaurant with a warm atmosphere in the heart of Greenpoint.

Good authentic, great tasting food with attentive service.

Outside seating available, also bar seating.
A favorite for the boys lunch on Fridays. We know lots of people there. It's a home away from home.
Just superb!
Best Fridays ever!

We arrived early evening which was a good thing to do as the restaurant does not accept reservations.
Quick and attentive service. I wasn't really hungry and so asked the waitress to suggest a dish that was not too filling and I ended up with the Prawn Curry that was excellent with a sauce that was not too spicy. My friend had a Ceasur Salad that looked enough for two.
A nice experience sat outside watching the world go by
Awesome and great vibe 👌
Food was very good, service was very helpful.  We needed to leave early; the chef and wait staff promptly prepared our takeaway for us.

Very tasteful dinner for all four of us, with all separate plates. Plating was a bit simple without veggies but these could be ordered. Good portions, great service 👍 but a little noisy.

Хороший ресторан. Прекрасное обслуживание.
Еда хорошая, но мне не хватило вкуса... Специй может быть или что-то такое.
В целом, это вкусовщина.

reviews_data.review_text: Delicious food, I recommend the prawn curry. It gets very busy and loud however, so get ready to use your voices when going there.
The food was delicious and good service.
A balance between a pub & a restaurant, a pleasant experience

had a terrible time at Mano's was dining alone waiting for a friend and ordered a chicken liver pasta, I got full quite quickly and asked the waitress to pack it to go. I literally ate a quarter of it...apparently she didn't hear me and assumed it was to be thrown away...three quarters of a mediocre pasta but it was still my money and I was going to eat it! I was too tired to fight so I let it go and didn't tip the girl.
The service there is generally substandard but its a cute place so you let it slide, is there a reason why there are ONLY white waitresses there??

Comida de excelente qualidade, atendimento esperto apesar muito jovem. Voltaria para experimentar outras coisas do menu. Vale a visita, até mais do que alguns outros restaurantes bem avaliados no V&A Waterfront, que não podem se comparar ao Manos. É bom e tá sempre cheio.
Owner very arrogant and extremely rude !!!

Amazing service and atmosphere. The place was very crowded so reservation is recommended.
The menu is simple but every order was on point. My fav was chicken preggo roll.
Even the side dishes are very good

Great food. Always served piping hot!
Superb service by the team. Always relaxed and
A favourite restaurant of ours due to the service, choice of food / quality and good portion sizes.
A nice restaurant in Green Point.... Relaxed atmosphere, ok food, ok prices... Service very good!
Best food and very attentive staff. Mano and Evie are excellent hosts.
The food is tasty the staff professional and it is in Cape Town - so 3/3

reviews_data.review_text:
Service 4/5
Atmosphere 3/5
Food 1/5 - probably the worst arrabbiata sauce I’ve ever had. Most of the main dishes I’ve had here have been really bad with far too much sugar or sweetening agents in their sauces and bastings. The only thing maybe worth going back for would be the chicken livers. I used to be a regular but in the last few years they have really dropped the ball. A lot to improve at Manos.
Lovely place to have a Prego roll before the Stormers/Lions game. Waitresses were superb and food hit the right spot. General ambiance excellent!

Wonderful waitstaff, but the manager was not receptive to feedback about the food (given only to try and improve the experience for future clients). He seemed stoic and unapologetic. Honestly think he should not be working in the hospitality business. As someone who has worked in the hospitality business before, I would’ve fired him.
Manager arrogant and not listening to clients. Not giving attention to feedback made in goodwill about food. Dissapointing.
Best food in Cape Town? No fuss, just honest to goodness quality.
Solid spot, food is flawless, service is great.
Well established local restaurant with great, charming service. Seafood dish was good, not memorable and the lack of vegetarian food options the reason why I'd only return, if a meeting requests it.

reviews_data.review_text:
They really do mean "dedicated to friends". Not only does the place have an amazing atmosphere and service it also comes with food that is beyond exquisite.

Treat your family, friends or significant other the next time you're in Cape Town.
We ordered 3 burgers and they were delicious. Lovely place to hangout with friends.

First impressions last, and within 2 minutes of arriving  not impressed. Today's we can smoke on the patio   Went back again, even worst. And we can smoke, ashtrays are broughtnot us then we can't anymore.  Thanks I'm good. No more Mano's for me
Presentation of the menu was lackluster. I would have preferred a more sophisticated and well presented menu. Overall great restaurant
Nice place. Right at the main road green point, short menu but fine. Service good just probably small but overall nice.

reviews_data.review_text:
The baked chicken oregano and the Greek salad are to die for.
Traditional home cooked stuff and a really cool owner.
Waitresses are very friendly and very attentive.
The restaurant itself is very simple and relaxed, but can get very loud when the restaurant is full.
The coffee is surprisingly very good.

Parking is available all around.
Long established no frills establishment serving great food at low low prices!
We had such a lovely experience at manos. They make a great chicken prego and have excellent service! A big shout out to our waitress Jade, who was sensationally helpful and accommodating!

Come on, just have a look at the pictures
... Mano's is exceptional! Best crayfish tails I have had. Everything we tasted was exceptional, calamari, ribs just everything! Food made with real soul & expertise. The Greek salad is very authentic, it comes to the table neatly presented altough it's best served all mixed together!
Amazing service, amazing atmosphere and fantastic food. Definitely worth a visit.
Lovely place for a bottle of wine! The halloumi was great too!! Server was great!
Consistently good food. A small menu, but every dish is a classic. Will not disappoint. Service is attentive but not overbearing. Pricing is fair.
Great atmosphere and very well priced. The waitress recommended the Penne Salmone and it was delicious and the portion size is perfect. Thanks Mano’s for a great lunch.

Always friendly staff, good food and love the Greenpoint vibe. Enjoy the people watching. I had the chicken lemony on spinach and ordered savory rice on the side. The dish is tasty and very lemony but very bland and unattractive looking. 2 Guests in our party had the baby chicken and absolutely raved about it.

reviews_data.review_text: Fair food ... but not my kinda crowd and atmosphere. Undesirable kind of people frequent this place... and the staff make you feel like they doing you a favour by serving you.
A very popular restaurant in Greenpoint. It is a trendy place and the food is world class. I love the baby chicken. We tried the creme brûlée and also was 10/10.

One of the best restaurants in Cape Town. The Fillet Prego Roll is incredible. Amazing atmosphere, with a lovely visit from the owner, Mano, great service, and exceptional food. Highly recommend coming here!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Grilled Calamari, Prego Roll, Chicken Ceasar Salad, Grilled Prawns, Chicken Schnitzel

reviews_data.review_text: Great food!
Trendy and lively. The food was good but pricey if one is not an international tourist.
Had great Calamari and enjoyed the vibe. Owner present and service reflected this.

The waitresses are nice, the young guy „being in charge“ should not work ( lets better say: being present!) in the service business! His promise the next available table outside is ours- forget it! Preferred chatting with his pals. And it was not that he was busy because the place was crowded. The food was ok, nothing special-except the spinach side order- my recommendation: don’t order it unless you like spinach which seemed to be a carton of frozen spinach just being heated up and being served- no spices- no taste!
Cape Town's best restaurant!!Need I say more?Great service,delicious food and very central.
Very good pasta

Cosy. Friendly staff.
Burger I had was delicious. Coming back for just the burger...

Would give 10 ⭐️ if possible. It has been years since we last visited Mano's and the evening was just as incredible as the time before. The service is excellent with neat and tidy waitrons serving with ease and grace. Each mouthful was a taste sensation, our plates were all cleaned completely. I will ensure it is not years before we return. Be sure to arrive early as there is no table booking system. So chill at the bar with drink in hand otherwise. Very lovely evening all round.

We popped into Manos for a light lunch on our first day in Cape Town as it was a short walk from our guest house.  The food, wine, staff and ambience were all great and we either ate or popped in for a drink pretty much every day of our visit.  The menu is small but everything we tried was top notch with great service from the very friendly staff.

What a great experience. The service was friendly and relaxed. The pasta salmone was one of the best I had, amazing - as your pasta cools down the salmon sauce thickens slightly with help of the shaven Parmesan. A good  wine companion for me for this dish was the Paul Clover Sauvignon Blanc. Love the good and energy.
Never disappoints
food is always top notch..try the lamb chops and peasant salad.
Fried calamari was poorly fried and had no taste. I ordered the chicken schnitzel and it was very bland as well. You’re better off air frying schnitzel from Woolies at home.

The thing that makes this restaurant so special is its consistency. The waiters are always good and quick service is given, the menu hasn’t been changed in years and doesn’t need to be they have perfected their meals. Their deserts are also something to take note of. Best creme brulee in town!!!

review_questions.Recommended dishes: Grilled Calamari, Prawn Curry, Prego Roll, Tempura Prawns, Beef Medallions

reviews_data.review_text:
Great place
Service is quick and friendly
Can't beat Mano's. Literally one of Cape Towns very best. Next level seafood!
Loved our food I had Mozambiqucan BBQ prawns and it was creamy and a bit spicy like I imagined and the rice was soft and tasty. Absolutely loved it

Dull, featureless atmosphere. Terrible service, waitress was very unfriendly and gave us attitude without obvious reason. Food took over 20 minutes to arrive and when it did, I could not enjoy my meal because the over-sized manager was leaning on my table talking to some other customers. When I complained I got a very insincere apology. Food tasted ok though
Good food and helpful staff. Recommended.

Nice location but guests without behavior
I would‘nt come back

I used to love this place and wanted to celebrate new years with a nice meal with a special friend.
Waiting for my friend enjoying some nice bubbles a very arrogant manager (Shaun ?) Insisted on cranking up some awful music to make conversation outside of shouting impossible ..he refused any request to lower so I left.
Manos was never like this
Never again which is a shame
